The three "big" offices:
Imperial Chancellor ("Magister Officorum")
- Watchdog of the administration
- Ranks as a comes
- Duties include:
   - Imperial Intelligence Service / Ambassadorial Bureau
- Four Bureaus under the Imperial Chancellery:
   - Clerical Bureau: handles decrees, appointments, imperial archive
   - Correspondence Bureau: handles correspondence from public officials, foreign service, translation
   - Legal Bureau: handles petitions and appeals
   - Arrangement Bureau: handles the administrative issues relating to the Emperor's travel
Magister Militum:
   - Supreme Commander
Patriarch
   - Should default to be HOF

Other subsidiary offices:
- Judge of the Imperial Court:
   - Handles administration of justice in the empire.
     Required to be well learned, head of chief tribunal, wrote laws
-  Count of the Imperial Treasury:
   - Collection of taxes, controlled the mints
- Count of the Imperial Estates:
   - Management of the Imperial personal estates
- Prefect of the City (Rome,Constantinople)
   - Handled the administration of the City & the Senate
- Praetorian Prefects
   - nominate individuals for office
   - Supervise governors
   - Dismiss governors

